replxx
------------------------------------------
A small, portable GNU readline replacement for Linux, Windows and MacOS which
is capable of handling UTF-8 characters. Unlike GNU readline, which is GPL,
this library uses a BSD license and can be used in any kind of program.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.1-1
  libgcc1-11.2.0-1
  libreplxx-devel-0.0.4-1bl1
  libreplxx0-0.0.4-1bl1
  libstdc++6-11.2.0-1
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.37-2
  cmake-3.20.0-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-11.2.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.2.0-1
  ninja-1.10.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/AmokHuginnsson/replxx

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/AmokHuginnsson/replxx/archive/refs/tags/release-0.0.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack replxx-0.0.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./replxx-0.0.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/replxx-0.0.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/replxx-0.0.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libreplxx0-0.0.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libreplxx-devel-0.0.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(replxx)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/replxx.README
  /usr/share/doc/replxx/LICENSE.md
  /usr/share/doc/replxx/README.md

(libreplxx0)
  /usr/bin/cygreplxx-0.dll

(libreplxx-devel)
  /usr/include/replxx.h
  /usr/include/replxx.hxx
  /usr/lib/cmake/replxx/replxx-config-version.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/replxx/replxx-config.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/replxx/replxx-targets-release.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/replxx/replxx-targets.cmake
  /usr/lib/libreplxx.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/replxx.pc

